ol.li:
There is a decomposition of the Hilbert space of a Free Scalar field as ℋ ϕ=⨁ n=0 ∞ℋ n \mathcal{H}_\phi = \bigoplus_{n=0}^\infty \mathcal{H}_n
where ℋ n=Sym nℋ \mathcal{H}_n = \text{Sym}^n \mathcal{H}
and ℋ\mathcal{H} is 1-particle Hilbert space described above (also known as the spin-00, mass-mm, irreducible unitary representation of Poincaré).

